# API Configuration
# Backend server URL for proxy configuration
# - For local development: http://192.168.4.79:37847 (external IP)
# - For Docker deployment: http://biller-simulator-app:8080 (container network)
# Default: http://192.168.4.79:37847
VITE_ENDPOINT_URL=http://192.168.4.79:37847

# Note: API authentication is handled via JWT tokens obtained from the login endpoint
# The JWT token is stored in localStorage after successful login and used for all authenticated requests
# No static API token is needed in the environment variables

# How the proxy works in different environments:
# - Development (bun dev): Vite dev server proxy rewrites /api/* to VITE_ENDPOINT_URL
# - Production (Docker): Nginx reverse proxy rewrites /api/* to http://biller-simulator-app:8080 (via Docker network)
# - Production (Vercel): Serverless function (api/proxy.ts) forwards /api/* using VITE_ENDPOINT_URL
# - Your frontend always calls /api/* (relative paths)
#
# API Architecture:
# - Administrative/Management APIs: /api/** prefix
#   - /api/login, /api/refresh (public auth)
#   - /api/users/** (ADMIN only)
#   - /api/overview (authenticated)
#   - /api/endpoint/**, /api/response/**, /api/biller/** (authenticated/ADMIN)
# - Dynamic Simulator Endpoints: Root level (/**)
#   - Examples: /inquiry, /payment, /check-status (public, no auth)
#
# For Docker deployment:
# - The backend URL is hardcoded in nginx.conf (line 29)
# - If you need to change the backend URL, update nginx.conf and rebuild the Docker image
# - Alternatively, you can use envsubst to template the nginx.conf at container startup
#
# For Vercel deployment:
# - Set VITE_ENDPOINT_URL as an environment variable in your Vercel project settings
# - The api/proxy.ts serverless function will use this environment variable
# - Fallback is hardcoded to http://192.168.4.79:37847 if not set